1
00:00:09,420 --> 00:00:12,340
(Public Security)

2
00:00:12,340 --> 00:00:14,300
(Qingcheng Public Security Bureau)

3
00:00:20,030 --> 00:00:21,000
Well, since you're here,

4
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,440
tell us about it.

5
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,640
About what? Stealing a dog?

6
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:27,190
It wasn't even a dog.

7
00:00:27,320 --> 00:00:28,760
We were framed.

8
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:30,670
You've been saying that all along.

9
00:00:31,550 --> 00:00:32,790
Say something new.

10
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:33,940
There's nothing else.

11
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:34,800
You sure about that?

12
00:00:35,150 --> 00:00:37,150
I said, "nothing else".

13
00:00:44,430 --> 00:00:45,570
What did you have for dinner?

14
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:46,440
Dinner? What dinner?

15
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:49,110
I got dragged here
before my livestream even ended.

16
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:52,200
Officer,

17
00:00:52,350 --> 00:00:54,640
I had tens of thousands
watching my stream today.

18
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,640
You have no idea how much money I lost.

19
00:01:02,150 --> 00:01:03,110
Besides,

20
00:01:03,710 --> 00:01:05,040
that woman started it.

21
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:07,120
You should go after her instead.

22
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,840
Don't play dumb with me.

23
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,480
You haven't had dinner?

24
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:12,560
Good thing you haven't.

25
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:17,780
=The Hidden Truth=

26
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,420
=Episode 3=

27
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:28,000
Thanks, Tang.

28
00:01:28,310 --> 00:01:29,790
If you hadn't arrived in time,

29
00:01:30,070 --> 00:01:31,790
anything could've happened.

30
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:34,270
Well…

31
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:36,400
Protecting people is our duty anyway.

32
00:01:36,950 --> 00:01:38,840
Just feels like we didn't do well enough.

33
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:40,710
Don't say that.

34
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:42,400
If it weren't for you today,

35
00:01:42,430 --> 00:01:43,870
I can't imagine what state I'd be in.

36
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:46,480
I've heard
those dog shelter folks are rough.

37
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,480
I didn't expect them to be even worse.

38
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:54,980
Um…

39
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,840
If something like this happens again,

40
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:58,590
don't rush in alone.

41
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,230
Call the police first.

42
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:02,990
Um...

43
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:05,280
Let's hope this doesn't happen again.

44
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:08,310
I just panicked
and didn't think it through.

45
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,640
But still,

46
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,590
I did call the police, didn't I?

47
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,800
Alright, your wound is treated.

48
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,680
CT results would be ready in three hours.

49
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,360
If you feel nauseous or unwell,

50
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,200
come tell us.

51
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:20,960
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

52
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,080
Th-thank you.

53
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,520
Hey, Cao, want a bowl?

54
00:02:38,610 --> 00:02:39,590
I'll pass, Captain Zhao.

55
00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:40,430
I'm on a diet.

56
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:41,960
Diet? What for?

57
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,310
It's delicious.

58
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:44,680
You eat first.

59
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,360
Alright.

60
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,240
Confess and you'll have dinner.

61
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:02,750
If you've got the skills,

62
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:04,590
bring the dog back for a match.

63
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,120
Without proof,

64
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,360
at most you'll detain me for 24 hours.

65
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,030
You seem familiar with the process.

66
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,800
Guess you've been here a lot.

67
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,050
By the way,

68
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:24,840
how did you figure out your lost dog

69
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:25,910
was at Hachi Dog Shelter?

70
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,120
I used to watch their livestreams

71
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:29,190
and followed their account.

72
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:30,800
After my dog went missing,

73
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:31,960
besides calling the police,

74
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,430
I posted a missing dog notice online.

75
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,400
Tonight, when I was scrolling my phone,

76
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,030
I happened to catch their livestream.

77
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:40,280
I saw Maodou

78
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,750
right on the screen.

79
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,560
Let's sit here.

80
00:03:47,870 --> 00:03:50,190
When I had a run-in with the shelter,

81
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:51,750
Maodou got frightened

82
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:52,840
and lost control.

83
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,630
He chased one of them and bit hard.

84
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,840
The bite was pretty serious.

85
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,910
Before I could stop it,

86
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,080
someone among them

87
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,840
deliberately opened all the dog cages.

88
00:04:02,030 --> 00:04:03,430
Several large dogs rushed out

89
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:04,870
and knocked me to the ground.

90
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,240
Are you sure?

91
00:04:08,470 --> 00:04:11,430
When we took everyone away,

92
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:13,680
I didn't see anyone injured.

93
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,800
Maybe he saw you coming

94
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,870
and slipped away quietly.

95
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,000
Could they have been dog thieves?

96
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,830
Maodou is very smart.

97
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,040
He's also highly alert.

98
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,630
Since they managed to take him,

99
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:28,000
they must be skilled.

100
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,160
Maodou only attacks those he resents.

101
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:33,630
I'll keep following this up.

102
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,000
If it really was the dog thieves,

103
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,870
we won't let them get away with it.

104
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:40,800
Maodou only hurt someone
because it got scared.

105
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,870
It's usually gentle and well-behaved.

106
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,390
Could you help me look for it again?

107
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,750
Don't worry, I'll do my best.

108
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:51,880
Really?

109
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:56,870
Thank you, Tang.

110
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,870
No problem.

111
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:04,110
Uh…

112
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,600
This might be a bit forward,

113
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:12,040
but I want to ask something personal.

114
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:13,960
What is it?

115
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,680
Did you grow up in a welfare home?

116
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:21,800
Welfare home?

117
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,440
Yeah.

118
00:05:26,390 --> 00:05:27,870
When I was little, I had a friend

119
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,040
who had the exact same birthmark as you.

120
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:40,560
She stayed in a welfare home?

121
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:44,710
Yeah.

122
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:47,630
We both stayed

123
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:49,310
at a welfare home for a while.

124
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,950
She was my best friend

125
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,310
and the one who treated me best.

126
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,560
She was younger than me,

127
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,800
but way braver than I ever was.

128
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:02,560
When I first arrived,

129
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,830
many kids picked on me.

130
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,440
Every time,

131
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,720
she was the first to stand up for me.

132
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:19,720
So, how did you two lose touch?

133
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,000
She got adopted?

134
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:28,110
As for...

135
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:31,240
the details,

136
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,630
I'm not really sure.

137
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:34,430
Anyway, she just left.

138
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,430
Not long after,
I also left the welfare home.

139
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:40,040
We never met again after that.

140
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:45,270
If she knew she had a friend like you,

141
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:46,510
still thinking about her,

142
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,390
she'd be very happy.

143
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:55,920
So...

144
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,310
that girl wasn't you.

145
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,560
Yimo.

146
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,510
Dad, I'm over here.

147
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:05,310
(Fourth Ward)

148
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:06,160
Did you get hurt?

149
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:07,310
Just a little scrape.

150
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,870
Don't worry, I'm fine.

151
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:09,910
A scrape?

152
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,210
Dad.

153
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:14,600
This is Officer Tang Tang.
He saved me today.

154
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:15,600
If it weren't for him,

155
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,270
things could've gone really bad.

156
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:20,430
Officer, I can't thank you enough.

157
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:21,280
You're too kind, sir.

158
00:07:21,290 --> 00:07:22,630
It's our duty.

159
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,310
Since you're here,
I'll head out first.

160
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:25,160
Still got work to do.

161
00:07:25,430 --> 00:07:27,480
Tang, I'm counting on you
to look for Maodou.

162
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,440
Don't worry.

163
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,410
I'll go now, sir.

164
00:07:29,410 --> 00:07:30,750
- Thanks, officer.
- No problem.

165
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:31,870
I'll buy you dinner sometime.

166
00:07:31,870 --> 00:07:32,830
No need to be so polite.

167
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:44,940
(Emergency Department)

168
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:58,120
What did you talk about with that officer?

169
00:07:58,430 --> 00:07:59,390
Nothing much.

170
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,270
Tang helped me out last time.

171
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,560
We exchanged numbers after that.

172
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,950
This time, I owe him again.

173
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:05,680
He helped you before?

174
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,510
At the farmers' market, a dog seller

175
00:08:08,510 --> 00:08:10,120
tried to snatch a mute woman's dog.

176
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,360
I stepped in,

177
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:12,270
and Tang saved me

178
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:13,310
from being beaten up.

179
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,510
Why do you care so much about him?

180
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,560
I just...

181
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:21,830
I think he really cares about you.

182
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,000
I'm getting jealous.

183
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,560
Dad.

184
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,630
Yeah, we can run a quick check.

185
00:08:33,270 --> 00:08:34,110
Master.

186
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:36,490
I went to the dog shelter again.

187
00:08:36,490 --> 00:08:37,750
I brought all the footage back.

188
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,960
How did it go? Did she talk?

189
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:44,840
They're all regulars.

190
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,840
Tight-lipped.

191
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:47,200
They know the rules

192
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,390
better than you do.

193
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,120
Let's wait for the dogs.

194
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:56,150
The girl who broke into the dog shelter...

195
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:57,600
Her name's Wang Yimo, right?

196
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:58,800
How was it?

197
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,390
She saw her dog

198
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,870
on a livestream

199
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:04,390
and rushed over without thinking.

200
00:09:04,630 --> 00:09:06,360
I checked the patrol officer's report.

201
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,200
It's true.

202
00:09:07,220 --> 00:09:08,550
I mean, how was she?

203
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:09,600
Was she hurt?

204
00:09:10,030 --> 00:09:11,750
Nothing serious, just some scrapes.

205
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,550
But she did mention something else.

206
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:14,510
When she arrived,

207
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,630
she saw her dog had bitten someone.

208
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,510
But among those we brought in,

209
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,390
none of them are injured.

210
00:09:24,910 --> 00:09:26,720
Focus on the footage from the time

211
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:29,030
Wang Yimo arrived at the shelter.

212
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:31,080
Find the person who got bitten.

213
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:32,230
I'm on it.

214
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,790
Keep watching, call me if anything's up.

215
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:02,480
Tang Tang, check this out.

216
00:10:11,060 --> 00:10:12,140
(Wednesday)

217
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:29,630
Captain Zhao.

218
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:32,800
Captain Zhao.

219
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:41,110
What happened?

220
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,720
We found that dog.

221
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:45,130
Really?

222
00:10:45,140 --> 00:10:46,870
Yeah, there's still blood on the its mouth.

223
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:48,020
- Got it.
- Okay.

224
00:10:58,750 --> 00:10:59,590
Take a look at this.

225
00:11:05,630 --> 00:11:06,750
The comparison's done.

226
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:09,790
You'll have to stay here
for more than a day.

227
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:12,910
Well, as long as I'm here,

228
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:14,550
I'll get paid.

229
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,840
Can't earn as much as you livestreamers,

230
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,240
but at least,

231
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,960
I can afford a meal when I'm hungry.

232
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,560
Captain Zhao.

233
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,240
Have something to eat first.

234
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:33,750
Look,

235
00:11:34,150 --> 00:11:35,670
speak of the devil and here it is.

236
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,480
Still warm.

237
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,350
Nice, really nice.

238
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,960
We didn't steal that dog.

239
00:12:00,510 --> 00:12:01,790
Someone sold it to us.

240
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,320
See?

241
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:06,120
There's still something to talk about.

242
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:09,390
We don't steal dogs.

243
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:11,240
We just transport them.

244
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,670
Then who sold them to you?

245
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,240
Two men.

246
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,750
Names, build,

247
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:19,120
appearance, accent.

248
00:12:19,390 --> 00:12:20,750
Our rule is simple:

249
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,480
Don't ask about who they are

250
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,870
or where the dogs came from.

251
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,630
They bring the dogs, we bring the cash.

252
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:30,590
Then we leave.

253
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:31,920
That's it?

254
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,840
That's it.

255
00:12:35,670 --> 00:12:36,870
What about the person

256
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,390
who got bitten by the dog last night?

257
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,600
I don't understand.

258
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:50,200
Didn't you bring all our people here?

259
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:51,790
No one got bitten.

260
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,270
You mean

261
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,240
someone not from your dog shelter

262
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:56,840
was there last night?

263
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,680
Who was that person?

264
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:01,390
How would I know?

265
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,630
What if they're sneaking around?

266
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:05,390
Officer,

267
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:07,600
I've told you everything I can.

268
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,630
You can't pin everything on me.

269
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,320
Buying a dog isn't illegal, right?

270
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:12,710
I bought my dog fair and square.

271
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:16,150
Do you think all pretty women are evil?

272
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,120
Did you notice something, bro?

273
00:13:26,270 --> 00:13:27,600
Yeah, I did.

274
00:13:28,270 --> 00:13:29,390
This isn't normal.

275
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,670
Normally they'd be streaming now.

276
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:34,200
Did something really happen?

277
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:39,110
Dude,

278
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,600
they're not gonna replace

279
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,510
my favorite female streamer, right?

280
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:43,350
Hey,

281
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,550
why do you always miss the point?

282
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:47,200
What's with that streamer thing?

283
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:49,510
That is the point to me.

284
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,640
She's the only one
who's ever said she loves me.

285
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,080
She's my first love.

286
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:57,230
Bro,

287
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,200
just listen to me for once.

288
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,000
We should focus on making money.

289
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:03,240
Once we've got cash,

290
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,390
I'll find you

291
00:14:05,630 --> 00:14:06,630
a good match.

292
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:10,870
Alright then.

293
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,320
That's more like it.

294
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,680
But right now,

295
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:15,360
we do have a problem.

296
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:16,790
We can't steal dogs anymore.

297
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,630
What, you're gonna deliver food now?

298
00:14:18,630 --> 00:14:19,840
Deliver food? No way.

299
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:22,030
The dog shelter's shut down.

300
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,870
Who would we sell dogs to?

301
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,960
We need to find a way to make money.

302
00:14:27,150 --> 00:14:29,000
You can't sit around like this forever.

303
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:30,750
Bro,

304
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,390
why don't we open a dog shelter?

305
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,200
Selling you wouldn't be enough
to open one.

306
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,510
You're full of useless ideas.

307
00:14:37,150 --> 00:14:38,480
If they don't livestream,

308
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,870
we do.

309
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:44,030
Forget it, I can't dance those moves.

310
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:47,390
Is it on?

311
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:48,910
Should we start?

312
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:49,750
Go ahead.

313
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:52,120
No one's watching.

314
00:14:58,540 --> 00:14:59,510
(Joined)
Someone's here!

315
00:15:00,130 --> 00:15:00,980
Welcome, welcome.

316
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:02,080
Welcome, my friend.

317
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,270
Please follow us.

318
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:10,750
Are you sure?

319
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,910
Testing DNA from the dog's mouth?

320
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,390
No one does that, Master.

321
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,800
Test it.

322
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:28,550
Old man,

323
00:15:29,510 --> 00:15:30,540
something's off about you.

324
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:33,630
You're hiding something from me.

325
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:34,910
Test it first.

326
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:37,240
We'll talk after the test.

327
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:22,870
The dog shelter has caught
the police's attention.

328
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,480
Looks like the plan needs to move up.

329
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,270
Here's your favorite pork trotter soup.

330
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:47,320
These flowers are pretty.

331
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,200
Put them on the windowsill? Saves space.

332
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:52,080
They're at their best right now.

333
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:53,270
I bought them to be admired.

334
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:54,510
Let's just keep them here.

335
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,160
They are beautiful.

336
00:16:56,630 --> 00:16:57,470
We'll do it your way.

337
00:16:58,670 --> 00:16:59,670
Smells amazing.

338
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:01,360
Here, have a taste.

339
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:04,870
Yimo.

340
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:07,640
When you graduated,

341
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:11,400
didn't you plan to study design in Paris?

342
00:17:12,270 --> 00:17:13,640
That wasn't my plan.

343
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:15,160
You're the one who insisted I go.

344
00:17:15,830 --> 00:17:17,440
You said with my major,

345
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,270
studying abroad would add value,

346
00:17:19,270 --> 00:17:21,240
and I could choose
Beijing or Shanghai after.

347
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:24,720
What is it, Dad?

348
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,200
Still not giving up?

349
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,440
I just feel

350
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:30,160
you should see more of the world.

351
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,240
How about

352
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,310
you come with me?

353
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:40,400
We could explore France together.

354
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,270
Visit some colleges

355
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:42,550
and have some fun.

356
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,510
You're always busy with restaurant work,

357
00:17:45,510 --> 00:17:47,200
and we've never traveled together.

358
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,720
I tried to persuade you,
but you wouldn't go.

359
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:53,680
Why the sudden change of heart today?

360
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,640
It's not that I didn't want to go.

361
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:58,030
I just didn't want to leave you alone.

362
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,790
Alright, I'll go with you.

363
00:18:03,070 --> 00:18:03,910
Nice.

364
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:11,860
(Incoming call)

365
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,080
Hello?

366
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,680
I gotta get to work.

367
00:18:45,030 --> 00:18:46,590
Didn't you say you'd stay home

368
00:18:46,590 --> 00:18:47,790
and spend some time with me?

369
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:48,990
Something urgent came up.

370
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,480
The restaurant needs me.

371
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,240
Take your time.

372
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:53,590
Come back early, okay?

373
00:18:53,790 --> 00:18:54,630
Sure.

374
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:08,380
(Dog Theft Case, Liu Yan Poisoning Case)

375
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,680
Have you seen him before?

376
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,080
No, I don't know him.

377
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,040
Time to go.

378
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,070
Move!

379
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,040
I...

380
00:20:18,590 --> 00:20:20,070
Why did I lose again?

381
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,110
Mr. Wang.

382
00:20:36,350 --> 00:20:37,350
What is this?

383
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,480
Take it

384
00:20:54,310 --> 00:20:55,150
and leave.

385
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:58,440
Last time, I didn't finish what I said,

386
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,550
yet you rushed off in a hurry.

387
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:03,550
We can talk a bit more this time.

388
00:21:06,350 --> 00:21:08,160
I've got nothing to say to you.

389
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,520
Take this

390
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:12,130
and get out of here.

391
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,510
Why the rush?

392
00:21:14,070 --> 00:21:15,880
I said I just wanted to catch up.

393
00:21:18,030 --> 00:21:18,870
Sorry.

394
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:20,680
I don't have time.

395
00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:23,400
Fifteen years of history.

396
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,720
Nothing to talk about?

397
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:30,070
What do you mean?

398
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:40,070
That's all the money?

399
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,440
It's not enough.

400
00:21:47,070 --> 00:21:48,400
I won't make things hard for you.

401
00:21:49,590 --> 00:21:50,920
I've got an idea.

402
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,270
You've lost your mind!

403
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:21,740
Still thinking about that?

404
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,240
It's not that I want to.

405
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:25,830
It's my new crew.

406
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,590
They want to grow the business.

407
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,960
A friend's friend is still a friend.

408
00:22:30,590 --> 00:22:33,270
So we need your help, Mr. Wang.

409
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:35,720
I'll never do that again.

410
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:37,590
Never.

411
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:40,590
You've already had fifteen extra years.

412
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:41,680
Be grateful for that.

413
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:46,880
You've had fifteen years of peace.

414
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,960
Seems you've forgotten
what's behind you.

415
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,200
I call you Mr. Wang

416
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:56,270
and you really think you have a choice?

417
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,720
You need to understand,

418
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:02,790
what you're doing

419
00:23:03,110 --> 00:23:04,790
isn't just paying off your own debt.

420
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:07,310
It's also for your…

421
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,160
daughter.

422
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,400
Such a young and beautiful girl.

423
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:21,160
She even loves puppies.

424
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,400
I really want to keep her safe.

425
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:33,880
If you lay a finger on my daughter,

426
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:37,150
you're dead.

427
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:42,100
(Hongyun Restaurant)

428
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,560
Ali.

429
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,480
Bai is back.

430
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:20,750
Wasn't he gone for good?

431
00:24:21,750 --> 00:24:22,880
No way.

432
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:26,030
He's been back for a while.

433
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:32,750
He asked us for a favor.

434
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:41,510
What's he planning?

435
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:51,240
The Nude Banquet.

436
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:56,720
Not a chance!

437
00:25:00,070 --> 00:25:00,960
I don't want in either.

438
00:25:14,070 --> 00:25:15,790
How's your mom doing now?

439
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:17,870
Not so great.

440
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:28,910
Qiang.

441
00:25:30,750 --> 00:25:32,640
No one knows what we did back then

442
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:34,830
better than you.

443
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:07,720
She's so young and beautiful.

444
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,160
I really want to protect her.

445
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:28,160
You know my mom's situation.

446
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:30,790
She's lying in the hospital.

447
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:33,350
Every single breath costs money.

448
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,070
If you want to go, go.

449
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:39,480
Qiang,

450
00:26:41,310 --> 00:26:43,160
we've worked together for years.

451
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:45,880
Can't you just give me a hand?

452
00:26:46,510 --> 00:26:47,590
I'll take less pay.

453
00:26:47,660 --> 00:26:48,640
Just enough for her med.

454
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,200
So all you care about is money?

455
00:26:53,310 --> 00:26:54,960
I'm not asking for it for myself.

456
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,070
You've got no parents,
so you wouldn't get it.

457
00:26:59,270 --> 00:27:00,480
It's been fifteen years.

458
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:03,400
You tired of living or what?

459
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:05,850
Zhang Ming, be careful

460
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:08,070
you don't die before your mom does.

461
00:27:18,350 --> 00:27:20,200
You think you can be off the hook?

462
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:31,200
You remember what we did, right?

463
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,480
You know Bai.

464
00:27:35,110 --> 00:27:36,070
Cross him again

465
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:38,270
and none of us will end well.

466
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,390
Even if money's not the issue,

467
00:27:46,350 --> 00:27:47,510
you don't want anyone here

468
00:27:47,510 --> 00:27:49,000
to get hurt, do you?

469
00:28:03,510 --> 00:28:04,510
As early as next week,

470
00:28:06,110 --> 00:28:06,950
we need to prepare.

471
00:28:14,660 --> 00:28:18,300
(Qingcheng Public Security Bureau)

472
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:23,980
(Dog Theft Case, Liu Yan Poisoning Case)

473
00:28:27,300 --> 00:28:29,940
(Lost, Poisoned, Theft)

474
00:28:29,940 --> 00:28:32,980
(Poisoning, Liu Yan Poisoning Case)

475
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:35,400
Alright, I got it.

476
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,560
Okay.

477
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:40,840
Master,

478
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,720
Liu's team finished checking Nan Village.

479
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:46,510
No leads on the dog thieves mentioned.

480
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:48,200
Looks like this trail's gone cold.

481
00:28:49,790 --> 00:28:51,680
If we can't confirm
the thieves' identity,

482
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,480
there's no way to link Liu Yan's case

483
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:55,270
to the Nude Banquet Case

484
00:28:55,270 --> 00:28:56,590
from fifteen years ago.

485
00:28:58,110 --> 00:28:59,400
It's alright, Master.

486
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,070
Big cases are always like this.

487
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,960
Whenever we hit a dead end,

488
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,480
we go back to the root of the problem

489
00:29:06,830 --> 00:29:08,270
and map out a fresh direction.

490
00:29:09,510 --> 00:29:10,750
You're taking it quite well.

491
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:12,520
Me?

492
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:14,830
Just trying to give us
a bit of confidence.

493
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:20,520
Master,

494
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:22,480
um… are you tired?

495
00:29:23,070 --> 00:29:24,440
If not, please tell me more

496
00:29:24,590 --> 00:29:26,270
about the Nude Banquet Case.

497
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:29,000
We could treat it
as reviewing the case.

498
00:29:29,160 --> 00:29:30,590
See if we've missed anything.

499
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:33,800
Liu Yan,

500
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:37,640
as one of the last arrested,

501
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:41,110
was identified only after the tycoon
admitted joining

502
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,680
the Nude Banquet.

503
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,350
The underage victims were all from

504
00:29:45,830 --> 00:29:48,350
he welfare home where Liu Yan worked.

505
00:29:49,590 --> 00:29:51,080
She acted as the go-between

506
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:53,070
for the welfare home
and the banquet organizers.

507
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:55,000
When we caught her,

508
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,030
she was about to flee.

509
00:29:56,270 --> 00:29:58,680
An officer pinned her down
at the train station.

510
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:00,200
From her statement,

511
00:30:00,750 --> 00:30:02,160
we learned that Bai's already dead.

512
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,750
Back then, she was

513
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:06,350
a crucial breakthrough in the case

514
00:30:06,590 --> 00:30:08,440
and also where the mystery began.

515
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:11,240
Her testimony connected to Bai.

516
00:30:13,750 --> 00:30:16,790
If she was poisoned to death,

517
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:19,160
not just an accidental ingestion,

518
00:30:20,070 --> 00:30:21,680
what was her link to the case

519
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:22,920
from fifteen years ago?

520
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,510
Did she leave something out

521
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,750
and someone wanted to silence her?

522
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:33,110
It's been fifteen years, Master.

523
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:35,170
She's been out of prison long ago.

524
00:30:36,270 --> 00:30:39,270
Why try to silence her now,
of all times?

525
00:30:40,350 --> 00:30:42,070
She witnessed Bai's murder.

526
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:46,830
The one who killed Bai killed her
to cover it up.

527
00:30:46,830 --> 00:30:47,880
That's one possibility.

528
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:50,240
But we can't rule out another.

529
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:52,680
At the scene where Bai was killed,

530
00:30:53,070 --> 00:30:55,110
someone else wanted her gone.

531
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:00,750
Someone else...

532
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:05,240
At that crime scene,

533
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:06,750
besides the murderer

534
00:31:07,270 --> 00:31:09,720
and her, the only witness,

535
00:31:10,070 --> 00:31:11,090
the only one left was...

536
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:12,910
the body.

537
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,590
Master.

538
00:31:17,510 --> 00:31:19,510
Was Bai's death confirmed back then?

539
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:20,680
Strictly speaking,

540
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,440
Liu Yan was the only witness.

541
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:32,750
Is there a chance Bai might be alive?

542
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,720
If I were Bai,

543
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,110
I survived,

544
00:31:46,110 --> 00:31:47,070
hid myself,

545
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:50,160
and even staged the murder

546
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,830
with my partners,

547
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:57,790
then that sole witness

548
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:02,240
would become my biggest threat.

549
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:07,310
Like I said before,

550
00:32:07,830 --> 00:32:08,720
we've got no evidence.

551
00:32:10,310 --> 00:32:11,310
Master,

552
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,680
even though that's true,

553
00:32:13,790 --> 00:32:16,200
your instincts are always spot-on.

554
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,590
If you think this way too,

555
00:32:17,590 --> 00:32:19,030
then chances are, it's real.

556
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:21,160
Once we catch those dog thieves,

557
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:23,030
everything will come to light.

558
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:24,560
Captain Zhao,

559
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,270
you might want to see this.

560
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:28,550
Right, Master?

561
00:32:42,220 --> 00:32:47,820
(Lost, Poisoned Sausage, Poisoned)

562
00:32:51,140 --> 00:32:54,060
(Lost, Poisoned Sausage, Poisoned)

563
00:33:05,620 --> 00:33:09,620
(Hongyun Restaurant)

564
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:14,260
(Hongyun Restaurant)

565
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,000
Zhang,

566
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:22,240
when we visited earlier,

567
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:23,830
the neighbors said

568
00:33:23,830 --> 00:33:25,160
the old lady is frugal.

569
00:33:25,350 --> 00:33:27,550
She cooks all her meals herself, right?

570
00:33:28,110 --> 00:33:28,950
Yeah.

571
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,620
(Hongyun Restaurant)

572
00:33:39,070 --> 00:33:40,640
Hongyun Restaurant.

573
00:34:22,740 --> 00:34:24,780
(Hongyun Restaurant)

574
00:34:49,060 --> 00:34:53,020
(Hongyun Restaurant)

575
00:34:59,500 --> 00:35:01,660
(Hongyun Restaurant)

576
00:35:20,230 --> 00:35:21,280
Hi, table for one?

577
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,760
This way please.

578
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:28,920
Here, what would you like to eat?

579
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:31,800
I'll browse first, order in a bit.

580
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:32,640
Alright.

581
00:35:41,110 --> 00:35:43,110
First time here, young man?

582
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:45,000
You should try their mapo tofu

583
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,400
and the stir-fried liver and kidney.

584
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:47,320
You won't regret it.

585
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:49,980
Alright, I'll go with your suggestion.

586
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,630
Business here is good.

587
00:35:52,710 --> 00:35:53,760
You're a regular, right?

588
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:55,630
Of course. Over ten years.

589
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:57,000
It's been open that long?

590
00:35:57,190 --> 00:35:58,360
Around fifteen years, I'd say.

591
00:35:59,510 --> 00:36:00,360
Look around,

592
00:36:00,630 --> 00:36:01,920
almost everyone here's a regular.

593
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:14,840
Mr. Wang.

594
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:17,710
Officer Tang.

595
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:19,960
What brings you here?

596
00:36:20,490 --> 00:36:21,360
What a coincidence.

597
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:22,240
Yeah, it is.

598
00:36:23,070 --> 00:36:23,910
Young man.

599
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:25,550
You already know the owner.

600
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,000
So all those questions?

601
00:36:28,030 --> 00:36:29,150
So this is your restaurant?

602
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,360
He's very kind,

603
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,840
praising how great your food is.

604
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:34,030
He was recommending dishes.

605
00:36:35,550 --> 00:36:36,800
He's a long-time customer.

606
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:37,640
Wow.

607
00:36:37,730 --> 00:36:38,590
Have you ordered yet?

608
00:36:38,590 --> 00:36:39,430
Not yet.

609
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,550
Leave it to me.

610
00:36:41,550 --> 00:36:43,550
I'll get you our best signature dishes.

611
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:45,500
This meal's on me.

612
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:46,430
But this doesn't count

613
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:47,480
as what I promised before.

614
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:50,440
I'll properly thank you another day.

615
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:52,800
No need, really.

616
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:54,400
I just came for a quick bite today.

617
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,760
I still have to head back to work.

618
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:57,960
What, you're here on duty or something?

619
00:36:58,190 --> 00:36:59,670
No, just passing by.

620
00:37:00,230 --> 00:37:02,360
Your place seems to be the busiest.

621
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:04,000
So I came for a quick lunch.

622
00:37:04,670 --> 00:37:06,840
Next time, when I'm off work,

623
00:37:07,100 --> 00:37:08,150
I'll have a drink with you.

624
00:37:08,150 --> 00:37:09,150
Go ahead, don't mind me.

625
00:37:09,150 --> 00:37:10,230
I'll just grab a quick bite.

626
00:37:10,230 --> 00:37:11,960
Alright, next time it's on me.

627
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:12,880
Okay?

628
00:37:12,970 --> 00:37:14,110
- It's on me.
- Go ahead.

629
00:37:17,780 --> 00:37:19,500
(Hongyun Restaurant)

630
00:37:20,110 --> 00:37:21,070
Have some tea first.

631
00:37:24,110 --> 00:37:25,400
Welcome. Please, come in.

632
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:26,800
No formalities, we're regulars.

633
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:34,120
Bro.

634
00:37:34,710 --> 00:37:35,550
Bro.

635
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,510
What are you two doing here?

636
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:42,800
Came to grab some food.

637
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:44,030
We're here to support you.

638
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,590
Eat up, then head out quick.

639
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:48,360
Not offering a drink?

640
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,120
In your dreams.

641
00:37:55,900 --> 00:38:00,060
(Cashier)

642
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:06,630
Dude, this place really is fancy.

643
00:38:06,630 --> 00:38:07,510
The food is amazing.

644
00:38:08,110 --> 00:38:09,920
Fancy restaurant? You call this one?

645
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:11,590
You really have low standards.

646
00:38:12,590 --> 00:38:14,400
You've never seen the world.

647
00:38:14,710 --> 00:38:15,840
If we hadn't stolen dogs,

648
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,000
we'd still be starving.

649
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:19,550
What? Serving dogs?

650
00:38:20,150 --> 00:38:21,030
It reeks, man.

651
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:25,030
You just want

652
00:38:25,030 --> 00:38:26,480
the whole world to know what we do?

653
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:29,710
Can't you eat quietly for once?

654
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:30,800
Bro,

655
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:32,840
I'm gonna criticize you.

656
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:35,320
You know that... that line

657
00:38:35,510 --> 00:38:36,510
from that movie?

658
00:38:36,590 --> 00:38:38,320
"You gotta love the job you're in".

659
00:38:38,590 --> 00:38:40,400
So why don't you have any passion?

660
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:41,510
Yeah, yeah, save it.

661
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:14,260
(Master)

662
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:27,960
I followed them all the way here

663
00:39:28,070 --> 00:39:29,880
but lost them inside a building.

664
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:30,880
I now suspect

665
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:32,480
this might be their hideout.

666
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:34,360
I checked out the surroundings too.

667
00:39:34,710 --> 00:39:35,550
An old neighborhood.

668
00:39:35,710 --> 00:39:36,760
Aside from elderly folks,

669
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,760
most are people from other areas.

670
00:39:39,070 --> 00:39:40,400
The crowd here's pretty mixed.

671
00:39:41,710 --> 00:39:43,070
You sure those two

672
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:44,800
are the dog thieves?

673
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:46,550
I can't say one hundred percent.

674
00:39:47,070 --> 00:39:48,440
But I'm sure they're involved.

675
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:50,440
I think right now,

676
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:52,160
this spot

677
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,880
could be our new lead.

678
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:55,800
It's worth a try.

679
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:57,120
Alright.

680
00:39:58,630 --> 00:39:59,630
Let's follow this lead.

681
00:40:06,540 --> 00:40:07,900
(Hongyun Restaurant)

682
00:40:09,030 --> 00:40:09,870
And...

683
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:11,160
What is it?

684
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:12,960
Why stop mid-sentence?

685
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,320
Who pulled your tongue?

686
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:15,600
No one.

687
00:40:16,230 --> 00:40:17,360
Let's follow this lead.

688
00:40:47,100 --> 00:40:49,020
(Dad, what time will you be home?)

689
00:41:22,900 --> 00:41:26,700
(Welcome to Hongyun Restaurant)

690
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:41,030
Dad.

691
00:42:08,790 --> 00:42:14,280
♪Dreams of the past sleep in the chill♪

692
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:17,730
♪Now I run toward the light♪

693
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:24,840
♪What does the fire burn,
what does it reveal?♪

694
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:28,810
♪Is the answer found when the sun rises♪

695
00:42:29,420 --> 00:42:33,710
♪If it's all a lie♪

696
00:42:34,900 --> 00:42:39,070
♪Should I tear it open?♪

697
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:45,120
♪If it's all part of the journey♪

698
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:50,650
♪Then face the blaze head-on♪

699
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:55,510
♪Let the sun awaken my heart's crave♪

700
00:42:56,050 --> 00:43:01,780
♪Pain reminds me I'm alive♪

701
00:43:01,900 --> 00:43:06,710
♪The world can't take away every clear sky♪

702
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:12,510
♪The hotter it gets, the fiercer I fight♪

703
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:17,540
♪Let the sun burn away all I lean upon♪

704
00:43:17,880 --> 00:43:23,540
♪Leave me only what endures♪

705
00:43:23,650 --> 00:43:29,200
♪At the cliff's edge, all fear shatters♪

706
00:43:29,260 --> 00:43:36,210
♪With a grounded heart, a soul like fire♪
